<!-- Default translations -->
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>(The song is the one that comes into your head when you hear the word &lt;a2&gt;“Charleston.”&lt;/a2&gt; It was composed by James P. Johnson, an African-American and one of early-20th-century's greatest masters of composition.)</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="ZH-CN" changeid="Cyy" changedate="20220218T074036Z" creationid="Cyy" creationdate="20220218T074036Z">
        <seg>（那首歌就是你一听到“查尔斯顿”这个词马上就会出现在脑海里的《查尔斯顿》，作曲为 James P. Johnson —— 一位非裔美国人，20年代早期最伟大的作曲家之一。）</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>However, the step had been around awhile before that.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="ZH-CN" changeid="Cyy" changedate="20220218T074132Z" creationid="Cyy" creationdate="20220218T074132Z">
        <seg>然而，其实在这之前，一切便早已开始。</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>In the 1900s, new American musical forms began to emerge from the Black and Creole communities of New Orleans in popular culture — first ragtime, and then early “hot” jazz — were no exception.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="ZH-CN" changeid="Cyy" changedate="20220218T034702Z" creationid="Cyy" creationdate="20220217T100034Z">
        <seg>1900年代，诞生于新奥尔良（New Orleans）黑人和克里奥尔（译者注：克里奥尔，Creole，路易斯安那州的法国移民后裔。）社区的新流行音乐文化——起初是拉格泰姆（ragtime），紧接是备受欢迎的早期爵士——亦非例外。</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>In the world of street dances, the music always comes first.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="ZH-CN" changeid="Cyy" changedate="20220217T094959Z" creationid="Cyy" creationdate="20220217T094959Z">
        <seg>在街头舞蹈的世界里，音乐总是先行出现的。</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>It was in the middle of the 1920s, when the jazz age was going strong, that America encountered one of its first and greatest nation-wide fads: &lt;s0&gt;The Charleston.&lt;/s0&gt; That was in 1923, when it was danced on the stage to a song in the popular all-Black Broadway show &lt;e1&gt;Runnin' Wild&lt;/e1&gt;.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="ZH-CN" changeid="Cyy" changedate="20220218T073432Z" creationid="Cyy" creationdate="20220218T071533Z">
        <seg>1920年代，当爵士风暴愈发强劲，美国迎来了史上第一次，也是最伟大的一次全国潮流：&lt;s0&gt;查尔斯顿（The Charleston）。&lt;/s0&gt;那是在1923年，伴着备受欢迎的全黑人阵容百老汇大秀《Runnin' Wild》中的一支曲子，查尔斯顿首次进入了公众视野。</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>It wasn't simply coincidence the song and dance were named “Charleston.” Johnson had seen the step done as early as the 1910s, when he was improvising piano music for dancers at clubs — most of the dancers doing the step had come from Charleston, and so he called the dance songs he wrote for them “Charlestons.” Other Black performers from South Carolina had done similar steps often enough they were referred to as “geechie” or “gullah” steps, a specific Black culture of Charleston and the low country.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="ZH-CN" changeid="Cyy" changedate="20220218T081035Z" creationid="Cyy" creationdate="20220218T081035Z">
        <seg>这首歌以及这种舞蹈叫“查尔斯顿”并不是一个简单的巧合。Johnson早在1910年代为俱乐部里的舞者即兴伴奏时就已经看到过这种舞步 —— 大部分跳这种舞步的舞者都来自查尔斯顿（译者注：南卡罗莱纳州的一座城市），因此他称自己伴奏的那些曲子为“查尔斯顿曲”。其他来自南卡罗莱纳州的黑人表演者也经常跳一些类似的舞步，他们称之为“吉奇步（geechie）”或“嘎勒步（gullah）”，一种来自查尔斯顿和南卡罗莱纳低地（Lowcountry）的特殊黑人文化。</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Made in Carolina</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="ZH-CN" changeid="Cyy" changedate="20220218T074200Z" creationid="Cyy" creationdate="20220218T074200Z">
        <seg>卡罗莱纳（Carolina）制造</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Many regional, and soon nationwide, dances began to evolve to this music.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="ZH-CN" changeid="Cyy" changedate="20220218T070108Z" creationid="Cyy" creationdate="20220218T070108Z">
        <seg>很多区域性的，并且在不久后传播至全国的舞蹈开始受到这种音乐的影响。</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Music Comes First</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="ZH-CN" changeid="Cyy" changedate="20220217T094915Z" creationid="Cyy" creationdate="20220217T094915Z">
        <seg>音乐先行</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>People hear a new music form start to arise, and it's only a matter of time before they begin to move to it.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="ZH-CN" changeid="Cyy" changedate="20220217T095152Z" creationid="Cyy" creationdate="20220217T095152Z">
        <seg>每当一种新的音乐形式开始兴起，人们伴着这种音乐舞动就只是时间问题了。</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>This is a series for beginner dancers.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="ZH-CN" changeid="Cyy" changedate="20220217T094830Z" creationid="Cyy" creationdate="20220217T094830Z">
        <seg>这是写给新人舞者的一系列文章。</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
